## Summary

\`AuthManager\` silently falls back to unencrypted remember cookies when the Encrypter service is not bound in the container. The remember cookie contains user ID, remember token, and password hash — all sent in plaintext.

## Location

\`packages/auth/src/AuthManager.ts:202-210\`

## Root Cause

\`\`\`typescript
let encrypter: any = undefined
try {
  encrypter = this.container.make(ENCRYPTER)
} catch {
  // Encrypter not available — remember cookies won't be encrypted
}
return new SessionGuard(name, provider, encrypter)
\`\`\`

No warning is logged. The developer has no indication that sensitive data is being sent unencrypted.

## Impact

User IDs, remember tokens, and password hashes transmitted in plaintext cookies if encryption is not configured. HttpOnly and SameSite flags mitigate XSS but not network interception.

## Suggested Fix

Log a warning when the encrypter is unavailable:
\`\`\`typescript
} catch {
  console.warn('[Mantiq] Encrypter not configured — remember cookies will NOT be encrypted. Set APP_KEY to enable encryption.')
}
\`\`\`

Consider refusing to set remember cookies without encryption, or at minimum exclude the password hash.

## Severity

**Medium** — sensitive data exposure in cookies
